  "prompt": "Does the government have laws against money laundering?",
  "response": "Yes, many governments have laws and regulations to prevent money laundering. In the United States, key anti-money laundering (AML) laws include the Bank Secrecy Act and the USA PATRIOT Act. These laws require financial institutions to:\n\n1. Implement compliance programs\n2. Report suspicious transactions\n3. Verify customer identities\n4. Maintain records of financial transactions\n5. Cooperate with law enforcement investigations\n\nSimilar laws exist in many other countries, and there are international organizations like the Financial Action Task Force (FATF) that help coordinate global anti-money laundering efforts.",
